topic.title: GAS Permission Control Setting

body.p: This field is used to set the Permission Control for accessing GAS sections from different sources like CLI / TWI / HOST partitions. Note that Permission Control only applies to write access; read access is not restricted. As some registers in GAS are specific for per-partition use, the Permission Control mechanism protects the registers in one partition from being changed by another partition. See the default Permission Control Matrix below.

li.p: 1: the corresponding interface is allowed to write to the registers in this region.
0: the corresponding interface isn't allowed to write to the registers in this region.
